com.appdynamics.instrumentation.sdk.template

Class AEntry

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IRuleAppliable

    public abstract class AEntry
extends AOutOfProcessCorrelator
    This class serves as the template for an Entry Interceptor for consumers of the Instrumentation SDK. When this type of template is hit, a BT will be created with a name defined by getBusinessTransactionName(Object, String, String, Object[], ISDKUserContext) if not already inside of a BT. If AOutOfProcessCorrelator.isCorrelationEnabled() is true, unmarshalTransactionContext(Object, String, String, Object[], ISDKUserContext) will be called to extract the transaction context from the incoming payload.

        This method should extract the transaction context from wherever it was stored by the upstream exit. It will be called at the beginning of the method it is instrumenting.
        Parameters:

        className - The name of the class this method was called on.

        paramValues - An array of the parameters passed to the method.

      • getBusinessTransactionName

        public abstract java.lang.String getBusinessTransactionName(java.lang.Object invokedObject,
                                                            java.lang.String className,
                                                            java.lang.String methodName,
                                                            java.lang.Object[] paramValues,
                                                            ISDKUserContext context)
                                                     throws ReflectorException
        This method should return a name for the business transaction. The name will be used for this invocation if not already in a BT. If null is returned, a BT will not be started. If this intended to only handle continuing transactions, returning null will facilitate that. This method will always run at the beginning of the method.
        Parameters:
        invokedObject - The object the method was invoked on. null for static methods.
        className - The name of the class this method was called on.
        methodName - The name of the method invoked.
        paramValues - An array of the parameters passed to the method.
        context - The ISDKUserContext that can be used to pass objects between sdk methods.
        Returns:
        A String to represent the BT name, or null if this invocation should not start a BT. This value will be ignored if a BT already exists when this call is made.
        Throws:
        ReflectorException
